{
  "text": "Early stage HCC patients have an indication for curative treatment including resection, liver transplantation, and RFA. It is important that the patient is indicated for curative treatments or not, but RFA cannot be performed due to liver hemorrhage for patients who have thrombocytopenia. Reports published on a number of cases define the indication for RFA as patients with a blood platelet count over 50,000/mm 3 [CITATION_1] or 40,000/mm 3 [CITATION_2] . Lusutrombopag acts selectively on human TPO receptors (c-Mpl) and activates signaling pathways that promote the proliferation and differentiation of bone marrow progenitor cells into megakaryocytes, consequently increasing the blood platelet count [CITATION_3] . In a phase III trial conducted in Japan, 77.1% of ",
